# Discord Chat Analysis for "core-devs" Channel

## 1. Summary:
The discussion primarily focused on operational changes and technical issues. Jin proposed changing a cronjob from daily to weekly for a newsletter and news show roundup, with a plan to merge announcement channels for cleanup. There was a concern about potential leaks of private information from the channel. Later, R0am shared information about Anthropic's discovery regarding ruler RL on MCP tool use, noting improvements in test accuracy for internal Slack tools (67% to 80%) and Asana tools (80% to 86%) through description and schema tweaks. A technical issue was reported regarding plugin API routes not resolving in version 1.5.8, but 0xbbjoker and Stan confirmed the functionality worked for them, suggesting the problem might be with the specific plugin route setup rather than the version itself. 0xbbjoker mentioned merging a pull request for the knowledge plugin to fix panel loading issues.
